<@!327354503563051011>.Items:
-Armoured Suit (20kn, 800°c resistance)

-3 daggers (15kn each)
-2 desert eagles (undetermined)
-Moon shaped blade (25kn)
-Mask with several functions
-Tracker with 2 chips.
-Foldable staff (kn determined by strength)

<@!280686912107315200>.Name: Lyon
<@!280686912107315200>.Items: His moms red sport car, Omen's Staff

<@!376563261317054474>.Name: Seyton

<@!376563261317054474>.Items: three kris daggers. They are light enough to be used as throwing knives, Steel baseball bat, A book filled with empty pages it’s titled: Happy, A necklace with a cross.

<@!305195849133064192>.Name: Miasma
<@!305195849133064192>.Description: A criminial turned hero in a big city that has much in store for her.
<@!305195849133064192>.Items: Tesla Gauntlets, Automatic Induction Device Mk1, Hardline Helmet, USBees

<@!389608227190341662>.Name: Xaphan
<@!389608227190341662>.Description: The dreaded villainess working with the Number 1 villain: Eddy.

<@!310863110951010306>.Name: Prometheus
<@!310863110951010306>.Description: A forgotten relic from a war long past brought back into a new era.

<@!389590546810929173>.Name: Teakettle
<@!389590546810929173>.Description: Oliver is a mess of contradictions. His friendly demeanor is at odds with his aversion to making friends; his contempt for the expectations placed upon him in his childhood didn't stop him from interning under Pharoahe; and despite his troubled heart, he wishes to do good, albeit in his own, selfish way. He also smells like warm milk, and not tea, as his hero name would imply.
<@!389590546810929173>.Items:
Oliver is equipped with nothing but his civilian paraphernalia, and a prosthetic right hand he got after an incident involving a rock, two bottles of soda, and a lot of screaming.

As for his apprenticeship, Oliver's been meaning to get himself some proper combat gear, but lacks funds; he's got a cheap padded armor, a mask, and a backpack to store his water bottles. But thanks to his mentor Pharoahe, he now has access to a "Protective Weave" Body Suit made of mutated hair and muscle fibers that can withstand 30kN of damage.

<@!565960962579103774>.Name: Eddy
<@!565960962579103774>.Description: Buckethead with a peculiar make-people-bleed fetish
<@!565960962579103774>.Items:
South's Helmet: Made of a quite durable alloy obtained from the scraps of felled Sentinels, the helmet protects him from damage to the head like helmets do and has become something of a symbol, an integral part of South's persona.

Long Fall Boots: Designed to absorb as much shock as possible when falling from great heights.

<@483438088954314753>.Name: System Aquamarine
<@483438088954314753>.Description: Baby AI who probably wants to watch the world burn

<@356540117462286337>.Name: Zephyr
<@356540117462286337>.Description: The space sidekick everyone wishes they had!

<@!368054928251289602>.Name: Polymouche
<@!368054928251289602>.Description: A man that can only really be described as a “theatrical serial killer”. He’s determined to make the city streets safe and make the city’s underbelly suffer to the beat of his blue suede shoes.

<@!456397930107109376>.Name: Sabine

<@!456397930107109376>.Items:
Set of sharp chakrams, a type of Sikh bracelet that is often used as a sharp throwing hoop. They are normally around her wrists. 25kN

Standard doctor's fare, including poisons. 

Sunglasses, jewellery, she dresses nice.

<@775971528961163305>.Name: Idolic
